WhatNew Buyer Protection Policy

WhatNew Support May 16, 2025 at 7:02 PM.

Buyer Protection — When buyers are entitled to a refund

Our Buyer Protection Policy covers the following issues, provided you submit your request within the specified timelines and the request isn’t excluded under the “Exclusions to WhatNew Buyer Protection” section:

  • Incomplete or incorrect items: one or more items are missing or incorrect.
  • Item not as described or inauthentic: items received are damaged, expired, defective, counterfeit, or do not match the condition description.
  • Package not received: items are lost, delayed in transit, not shipped, misdelivered, or not received after being marked “delivered” by the carrier.
  • Full list of covered issues under Additional Details (see below).

You must submit your request by the earlier of 30 days from purchase or{" "} 14 days from delivery for your request to be eligible under WhatNew Buyer Protection. Certain categories have specific deadlines:

  • Coins & Money, Sports Cards, Sneakers & Streetwear, Trading Card Games, Luxury Goods:{" "} Submit by the earlier of 7 days of delivery or 30 days from purchase.
  • Plants: Submit by the earlier of 2 days of delivery or{" "} 30 days from purchase.

How shipping works on WhatNew

This article explains how shipping charges are calculated for WhatNew orders. Examples are included to show how bundling and incremental shipping work during livestream purchases.

Shipping rate tiers (summary)

  • USPS First-Class Mail Letter Service (eligible items): for very light shipments that meet all eligibility criteria:
    • Weighs less than 3 ounces
    • Total value is less than ₹20
    • All enclosed items are cards from Sports Cards, TCG categories, or Stickers only
    • No more than 5 cards in the shipment
    • Order shipped from a US address to another US address
  • USPS Ground Advantage (commercial negotiated rates): Used for lighter packages (less than 1 lb) and for many zone-based shipments.
  • USPS Priority Mail (1–5 lbs): For packages weighing 1–5 lbs or when seller selects Flat Rate packaging up to 70 lbs — usually charged at a typical negotiated rate of ₹9.21 (₹8.77 + fees) for many mainland U.S. deliveries. (Hawaii, Alaska, U.S. Territories and military bases may be excluded.)
  • Packages 5–70 lbs: These ship via USPS Priority Mail by default, or Ground Advantage if opted into. Pricing is based on weight, distance, and dimensions — starting at roughly ₹8.91.
  • Dimensional weight: Items over 1 cubic foot will be charged by dimensional weight.

Illustrative example (livestream bundling)

Buyer in Los Angeles, CA purchases a pack of sports cards from a seller in{" "} Boston, MA.

  1. Zone: This counts as a cross-country shipment (example: Zone 8).
  2. Weight: Pack + packaging = 4 oz. Shipping cost (USPS Ground Advantage commercial rate) = ₹4.13.
  3. If buyer adds another 4 oz pack (now 8 oz total), additional charge = ₹0.31{" "} (so total shipping becomes ₹4.44 for the 8 oz package).
  4. If buyer then buys a pair of sneakers (2 lbs), the incremental shipping charged ={" "} ₹3.91, because the negotiated 1–5 lb rate is ₹9.21. Once the buyer has been charged ₹9.21, additional items from that same seller can be added at no additional shipping cost until combined weight reaches 5 lbs. After 5 lbs, we charge at-cost according to USPS Priority Mail rates.

Livestream-specific nuances

  • Sellers can offer Free or Reduced Shipping to cover some or all of a buyer’s shipping cost, or above a seller-defined threshold.
  • For shipments over 5 lbs sellers can choose Flat-Rate packaging or Ground Advantage instead of Priority Mail. Flat-Rate Shipping example: ₹9.21 (₹8.77 + fees); Ground Advantage pricing starts from{" "} ₹8.91.
  • WhatNew Smart Bundling™ will group and ungroup orders to keep shipping costs low — orders from a single seller may arrive in multiple shipments.
  • Marketplace purchases are bundled across marketplace orders, but they are not bundled with livestream purchases.
  • For very large items that don't fit within 1 cubic foot, dimensional weight pricing may apply and can be more expensive than a similarly weighted item that fits inside a 1 cubic foot box.

Note: Rate examples above are illustrative. Carrier pricing, negotiated rates, and fees may change; always refer to the live rate card or seller checkout for final shipping charges.
